Close
very heavy bleeding (around 50 mL fluid each day over 3 days using a menstrual cup); Moderate cramping/intense cramps; fatigue; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). A 26-year-old female patient received second dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, Solution for injection; Lot Number: ER8727) via an unspecified route of administration, administered in Arm Left, at the age of 26-year-old, on 27Mar2021 15:00, as SINGLE DOSE for covid-19 immunisation. Medical history included hypothyroidism, obesity, dysmenorrhea, moderate cramping and fatigue. The patient is not pregnant at the time of vaccination. The patient was not diagnosed with COVID prior vaccination. Concomitant medications included sumatriptan and levothyroxine sodium (LEVOTHYROXIN). The patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, Solution for injection; lot number EN6205) at left arm, at the age of 26-year-old, on 06Mar2021 13:00, for covid-19 immunisation. The morning before the vaccine, early period symptoms had begun reported as moderate cramping and fatigue. The patient waited 8 hours after vaccine to take Naproxen Sodium 540mg (a usual dosage for my usual period symptoms to be taken every 8 hours). On 28Mar2021, the day after vaccine, the patient saw some spotting but reduction in period symptoms. Three days after vaccine, the patient saw very heavy bleeding (around 50 mL fluid each day over 3 days using a menstrual cup), intense cramps even with 540mg naproxen, and fatigue that required sleeping most of the day. While this combination of symptoms is a normal occurrence for the patient, the symptoms this time is at a greater magnitude than normal, and these symptoms came in and out over five days from start of bleeding, three days longer than is normal for the patient. The patient underwent lab tests and procedures which included sars-cov-2 test: negative on 07Apr2021. Outcome of the events was recovered in 2021.

Close
Jaundice of skin and eyes, symptoms of anemia (shortness of breath, extremity tingling, difficulty exercising), dark urine, yellow tinged stool, yellow tinged body fluids, shortened menstruation. Physically noticed symptoms in early February 2021. Symptoms did not improve so scheduled a clinic visit. Lab tests revealed critical low H&H with no signs of hepatic malfunction or disease. ER visit and consultation with hematologist pointed to diagnosis of Warm Autoimmune Hemolytic Anemia. No family history of autoimmune disease, no previous history of condition, no previous cancer, no prescription medication. Suspect that the vaccine caused condition. Current treatment is high dose prednisone. Treatment ongoing.

Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethic committees, and Investigators, as appropriate,Linked Report(s) : US-PFIZER INC-2021458221 mother/baby case

My Pfizer shots were delivered on Feb 18 and March 12, 2021. I experienced irregular menstrual symptoms from March 1-March 13 of 2021. My typical menstrual cycle is 26-28 days, with 3-4 days of concentrated bleeding. My previous 3 periods were Dec 18-22. Jan 17-20, and Feb 12-16. On March 1 almost 2 weeks before my expected period, I started spotting and cramping. The light bleeding continued for 2 weeks, at which time it transitioned into my typical period with regular cramps and bleeding, in line with my usual experience. My GYN did not know what could be causing this (I later found out there have been many irregular menstrual symptoms associated with Covid-19 vaccines. I don't regret getting it, this was fairly mild, but if there is a causitive link between the vaccines and mesntrual side effects, women NEED to know this. Menstrual and female reproductive health side effects need to be observed and measured in clinical trials, and female patients need to be advised what to expect.

I am being followed on a weekly basis for blood draws by my obgyn office to ensure that my hcg hormone level falls to 0.

bleeding was getting heavier byTuesday I was already going through 10 large pads/blood was gushing out of me; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). A 38-years-old female (non pregnant) patient received first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 mRNA VACCINE, Solution for injection, Batch/Lot number: EW0183 and Expiration date: not reported), via an unspecified route of administration on 09May2021 at 10:00 (at the age of 38-years-old), as single dose for covid-19 immunization. Patient was not pregnant at the time of vaccination. Patient did not receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine. Prior to vaccination, patient was not diagnosed with COVID-19. Medical history included patient provided a list of medications that she was allergic to. Patient received unspecified prescribed medicines within 2 weeks of vaccination. Patient provided the nurse, that gave her the shot, the list of prescribed medicines that she was taking. Nurse told her that she was ok to take the vaccine and we proceed. After the vaccine patient waited 30 mins sitting down then she was ok to go home. On 09May2021 at 14:00 hours, patient noticed that towards the evening her bleeding was getting heavier by Tuesday (11May2021) and she was already going through 10 large pads by 10:00 am. Patient was told to laid down with her feet up by her mother as her husband was at work and stated that we were going to go to the hospital on the evening. When her husband came home, she stated that we decided that we were going to go on Wednesday (12May2021) morning to the hospital. Patient's husband woke up that Wednesday morning, she was still asleep and screamed at her "you crazy we need to go to the hospital right now". Patient was cover waist down in blood and stated that they told her to try to get up and she felt that blood was gushing out of her (hospitalization). Ambulance was called. Since the vaccination, patient had not been tested for COVID-19. Patient had emergency room/department or urgent care visit. Patient received tranexamic acid, birth control, medroxyprogesterone as treatment for the adverse event. The outcome of the event was not recovered.

patient was pregnant while taking BNT162B2; patient was pregnant while taking BNT162B2; Miscarriage 11 days post vaccine; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable Nurse. A 39-year-old female nurse reported that she received first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 mRNA VACCINE; Lot number EL0142), into the left arm on 28Dec2020 at 07:30 AM at single dose for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included asthma and eosinophilic esophagitis and allergies to Keflex ASA. Concomitant drugs were none. At the time of vaccination the patient was pregnant, her last menstrual date was on 20Nov2020, gestational period 6. The patient reported that on 08Jan2021 at 12:00 PM she had miscarriage 11 days post vaccine. The patient was seen at Doctor or other healthcare professional office/clinic visit. At the time of reporting the patient was recovering.; Sender's Comments: Based on temporal association, a possible contributory role of BNT162B2 cannot be completely excluded for reported miscarriage. However, information is limited, and miscarriage is multifactorial event. In the general population, the estimated background risk of miscarriage in clinically recognized pregnancies is 15% to 20%. The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees and Investigators, as appropriate.

A 39-year-old female patient received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE), via an unspecified route of administration, administered in the left arm, on 12Feb2021 17:30 (lot number: EL3249), as 1st dose, single; and via an unspecified route of administration, administered in the left arm, on 05Mar2021 13:30 (lot number: EL9265), as 2nd dose, single, for COVID-19 immunisation, at a clinic. Medical history included bleeding. The patient was not pregnant at the time of vaccination. The patient did not have COVID-19 prior to vaccination and was not tested for COVID-19 post vaccination. Concomitant medications included medroxyprogesterone acetate (DEPO-PROVERA) taken to prevent bleeding; buspirone hydrochloride (BUSPAR); omeprazole; cyclobenzaprine hydrochloride (FLEXERIL); and naproxen, start and stop dates were not reported. The patient previously took ciprofloxacin (CIPRO) and experienced allergy. The patient did not receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to BNT162B2. On 12Feb2021, the patient experienced immediate (very much unwanted) menstruation despite Depo-Provera to prevent bleeding. This was following both the first and second doses of COVID-19 vaccine. No treatment was given for the event. The outcome of the event was not recovered.

On 1/21/21, approximately 59 hours after I received the Pfizer\BioNTech COVID19 Vaccine #2 without any immediate adverse events, I woke up in the middle of the night with subjective fevers, sweats, chills, generalized weakness with dizziness and feeling faint, nausea, diarrhea, and severe pelvic/lower abdominal pain (though I was also in the process of starting my menstrual cycle). I also vaguely noticed an erythematous rash on my chest and abdomen at that time. I took a dose of ondansetron for nausea and acetaminophen for pain. Later that morning (1/21/21), I continued to have generalized weakness, subjective fevers and chills, extreme fatigue, nausea, and a morbilliform-type rash most prominently on my torso (chest, abdomen, back) and some areas of my upper arms and thighs, as well as bright red and hyperemic palms and soles that had a prickly sensation throughout. I no longer had abdominal pain, but did have significant polyarthritis with difficulty moving my joints without pain. This included my knees, elbows, ankles, wrists, as well as fingers/hands especially. My fingers and toes felt very swollen and I had trouble putting my normal enclosed shoes on. I took ibuprofen and Tylenol during this time for symptom control. Later I added diphenhydramine, loratadine, and famotidine. These symptoms waxed and waned in intensity for at least 8 days with continued spread of rash, extreme fatigue, ongoing joint pain, and subjective fevers. The only measured fever was on 1/23/21 when I had access to a thermometer - my oral temperature was 100.7F if I recall correctly. I never had any respiratory symptoms. On 1/29/21 I saw Hospital Allergist Dr in order to participate in a research study on adverse vaccine reactions; I did not have a formally documented medical appointment with her for my medical records. By that time, my energy level was slowly improving and I was able to return to work. My arthritis symptoms had nearly fully resolved, however, my rash had gone from not particularly bothersome to very diffusely pruritic. I began to take cetirizine for symptoms instead of loratidine. In addition, the skin along my L palm began to slough and peel off, most notably in the webspaces between my thumb and index finger bilaterally and the tip of my L thumb and L ring finger. These areas of my palm had the most notable peeling and sloughing around 2/2/21 and by 2/7/21 my R palm was also peeling in similar fashion to the L. On 2/11/21, I noticed that the skin along my L sole, particularly between all five digits had begun to peel quite markedly; large connected pieces of skin were sloughing off. The sloughing on the L foot spread from between the toes and the ball of the foot to the arch and then the heel over several days. On 2/14/21, the R foot/sole began having the same findings, with large amounts of sloughing first between the toes and then extending to the ball of the foot, arch, and ultimately the heel. Some sort of foot/sole peeling continued through the final week of February 2021 and into early March.

Roughly 16 hours after receiving the second dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccination I began experiencing abdominal cramping that I would normally associate with menstrual like cramping. The reason I found this to be abnormal is that I underwent an ablation procedure more than seven years ago and have rarely if ever experienced abdominal cramping since that time. Approximately two weeks after the injection I experienced what I could consider an abnormal menstrual cycle with bleeding that lasted four to five days. I found this to be strange considering I've not experienced any such menstrual cycle since undergoing the ablation more than seven years ago. Since the ablation procedure I could count the number of times, on one hand, when I've experienced any type of bleeding and those instances have produced such an insignificant amount of blood that I could not justify even wearing a tampon. In those handful of situations I spotted for 2-4 hours maximum. Fast forward two more weeks and here I am having a menstrual cycle and bleeding enough to wear a tampon.

Second Vaccine Location: Pharmacy. On 6/2/21 (day after 2nd dose) I vomited repeatedly throughout the day, a total of 4 times between 9am and 5pm and was unable to keep any water or Tylenol down at all. I had a strong headache the entire day, which also brought with mental fatigue and overwhelm - I couldn't even manage to watch tv I was so ill, it was hard to concentrate, think or even focus my eyes. Around 5pm, feeling severely dehydrated and realizing the urgent cares would be closing soon I scheduled a telehealth dr. appt. with assistance. (I couldn't sit up or focus long before being overcome with nausea, and it was very hard to think.)The telehealth dr. prescribed me anti nausea medicine - Ondansetron, orally disintegrating tablet, 4mg. Told me to attempt drinking 1tsp water every 10 min. after having the medicine. After taking this medicine and also a dissolving form of tylenol you could put on your tongue, and waiting another hour I was able to begin taking sips of water and sit up. I was able to drink more water over the next few hours and finally some cold plain cereal. I thought I was finally in the clear, however I was surprised that I continued to feel nauseous the next two days and continued to need to take the medicine prescribed (from 6/2 - 6/4). My stomach was so upset from nausea and also I had cramps from beginning my menstrual cycle, but I continued to have stomach aches for the following two days (6/2-6/5). I wondered if it was a side effect from the vaccine or the anti nausea medicine. I also experienced constipation 6/2-6/12, (up to the day of writing this) something I never have an issue with. While I could say it might be related to the medicine, I don't understand why it would continue so long. It has improved somewhat gradually. What was most surprising to me after all of this is I then began to experience having a stutter when speaking, approximately once a day every day since returning to work through June 8th. (6/4 - 6/8). While this might seem minor, I have not ever experienced this in my life, so four times in four days is markedly unusual.
